description.narrative: The objectives of the Project are to improve (i) the delivery of quality essential health and nutrition services and utilization bywomen and children especially among the poor and drought affected populations; and (ii) the effectiveness of planning, financing, and procurement of pharmaceutical and medical supplies.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Article V | Description :The Co-financing Agreement has been executed and delivered and all conditions precedentto its effectiveness, or to the right of the Recipient to make withdrawals under it (other than the effectiveness of thisAgreement), have been fulfilled. | Due Date :31-Jan-2014

Finance Agreement :Section I D. | Description :No later than April 30 each year, commencing on April 30, 2011, Health SWApSecretariat shall prepare and furnish to IDA through the PS MOPHS & MOMS for IDA's review, an annual work prog & budget | Frequency:Yearly
Finance Agreement :Section II A. 2. | Description :A Mid-Term Review would be carried out by December 31, 2012. | Due Date:31-Dec-2012

Finance Agreement :Section III E. 1. | Description :All training activities shall be carried out on the basis of plans and budgetssubmitted annually by MOMS & MOPHS for prior written approval of IDA. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Section III E. 2. | Description :MOPHS & MOMS would have recruited an independent integrated fiduciaryimplementation review agent under terms of reference acceptable to IDA by Dec. 31, 2010, now being amended to March 31, 2011. | DueDate :30-Jun-2011
